<TEXT>
the disease that gave wc fields one of the most 
famous noses in america can now be treated with a new drug its 
developers said wednesday 
metrogel developed by curatek pharmaceuticals inc of suburban 
elk grove village has won approval from the food and drug 
administration as the first prescription drug in the united states 
specifically for rosacea or adult acne 
the condition which researchers said gave fields his red 
bulbous nose affects people in their 30s and 40s and if 
untreated can lead to significant disfigurement 
most people with rosacea dont even know it is treatable said 
dr jonathan wilkin director of dermatology at ohio state 
university who joined curatek officials at a news conference 
announcing the drug 
fields entrenched the notion that people who have rosacea are 
abusing alcohol wilkin said but he added that while alcohol may 
aggravate the disease rosacea can be just as severe in nondrinkers 
wilkin also said no one really knows what causes the rosacea the 
condition can be reversed if caught in its early stages he said 
in fields case the disorder progressed to what is called 
rhinophyma a condition in which dilated pores on the nose become 
excess tissue that results in a bulbous red appearance wilkin said 
the most common treatment in the past has been oral antibiotics 
which tended to be ineffective or associated with adverse reactions 
like allergies nausea and yeast infections wilkin said you 
could never depend on those products he said 
wilkin said metrogel has little or no side effects 
metrogel with the scientific name metronidazole is a 
waterbased gel that is invisible odorless and can be used under 
makeup 
approved by the fda in november it is available by prescription 
at a cost of 14 to 20 for a oneounce tube said robert j 
borgman president of curatek 
wilkin said women are slightly more susceptible to rosacea than 
men but more severe cases are found in men and heredity also may 
play a role 
people at the greatest risk of rosacea are fairskinned 
individuals who flush easily and their condition may be triggered 
by a variety of factors including spicy foods he said 
</TEXT>
