to that of congress where the senate allows meals under 50 and the 
house meals under 35 
they also agreed that socalled double dipping laws limiting the 
pension that retired military officers can receive if they take 
civilian federal jobs ought to be revised so that military pensions 
were allowed to be taken in full if vested just like corporate 
pensions 
