unisys corp announced wednesday that it has 
dismissed 1700 people at 60 us locations as part of a major 
restructuring designed to reduce the computer companys work force 
by 3 percent this year 
the company also said from its headquarters in suburban blue bell 
that it will close a component assembly plant in nogales mexico at 
a cost of 400 jobs 
about 190 people at the companys headquarters were released 
wednesday and about 400 more will lose their jobs at the end of 
july when the company consolidates a computerdesign group at the 
headquarters with a larger division in roseville minn unisys said 
the second hardest hit location was the companys santa clara 
calif operation where disk drives are made the approximately 350 
employees affected there opted to work through a 60day notice 
period rather than leave immediately hynes said 
he said the reductions at the companys other us locations 
affected by the cutbacks involved fewer than 100 employees each 
the moves essentially complete the companys plans to streamline 
in 1989 in the face of weak results 
obviously this is a major restructuring that has brought us 
essentially into the range where we told people we wanted to be for 
1989 said j peter hynes a unisys spokesman 
after a presentation last week to securities analysts in new 
york unisys chairman w michael blumenthal said the company planned 
this year to reduce its work force of 93000 by 3 percent or about 
2800 people in addition the company plans to pare more than 500 
million from its inventories by midyear 
to be competitive we have got to reduce costs brutally 
blumenthal said 
about 100 of those released wednesday at the companys 
headquarters were computer design engineers hynes said the rest 
were in administrative and marketing positions 
hynes said only a small number of the affected employees 
would be transferred or rehired 
hynes said all employees released this week will receive six 
weeks pay in addition to a severance package all also are eligible 
for job counseling he said 
hynes said earlier that about 900 of unisys 68000 us 
employees have been offered early retirement so far this year 
on tuesday unisys introduced a longawaited line of mainframe 
computers designed by the engineering group in blue bell the new 
2200 series will replace the companys 1100 line the products 
release was delayed by several months hurting sales as customers 
postponed purchases until the new line was available 
layoffs are not new for the nations thirdlargest computer 
company which is the product of burroughs corps 48 billion 
takeover of sperry in 1986 since the acquisition unisys has pared 
18000 from its payroll through sales of operations and 12000 more 
through early retirements and layoffs 
last years acquisition of convergent inc a california computer 
maker added 3500 to the companys job rolls 
blumenthal acknowledged last week that it had been a tougher 
year than anticipated and that he expected a weakness in sales to 
continue in the first half of 1989 
sales in 1988 increased 2 percent from 1987 to 99 billion 
although unisys profits rose about 18 percent in 1988 most of the 
increase was attributable to lower tax rates not bigger profit 
margins the companys operating profits slumped by nearly 
onequarter in the final quarter of 1988 
at their meeting with wall street analysts thursday senior 
executives said they expected results from the first three months of 
1989 to be poor with no revenue growth largely because of the 
bottoming of the 1100 product cycle 
the second quarter will improve as the new computer line starts 
kicking in revenue while the third and fourth quarters will be 
exceptional they said 
